title: The Killing
overview: Crook Johnny Clay assembles a five man team to plan and execute a daring race-track robbery.

title: Touch of Evil
overview: A stark, perverse story of murder, kidnapping, and police corruption in a Mexican border town.

title: The Night of the Hunter
overview: A religious fanatic marries a gullible widow whose young children are reluctant to tell him where their real daddy hid the $10,000 he'd stolen in a robbery.

title: Out of the Past
overview: A private eye escapes his past to run a gas station in a small town, but his past catches up with him. Now he must return to the big city world of danger, corruption, double crosses and duplicitous dames.

title: Manbiki kazoku
overview: A family of small-time crooks take in a child they find outside in the cold.

title: Wind River
overview: A veteran hunter helps an FBI agent investigate the murder of a young woman on a Wyoming Native American reservation.

title: Dogville
overview: A woman on the run from the mob is reluctantly accepted in a small Colorado community in exchange for labor, but when a search visits the town she finds out that their support has a price.

title: Taxi Driver
overview: A mentally unstable veteran works as a nighttime taxi driver in New York City, where the perceived decadence and sleaze fuels his urge for violent action by attempting to liberate a presidential campaign worker and an underage prostitute.

title: The Godfather
overview: An organized crime dynasty's aging patriarch transfers control of his clandestine empire to his reluctant son.

title: The Departed
overview: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

title: Inside Man
overview: A police detective, a bank robber, and a high-power broker enter high-stakes negotiations after the criminal's brilliant heist spirals into a hostage situation.

title: Blood Simple
overview: The owner of a seedy small-town Texas bar discovers that one of his employees is having an affair with his wife. A chaotic chain of misunderstandings, lies and mischief ensues after he devises a plot to have them murdered.

title: True Romance
overview: In Detroit, a lonely pop culture geek marries a call girl, steals cocaine from her pimp, and tries to sell it in Hollywood. Meanwhile, the owners of the cocaine, the Mob, track them down in an attempt to reclaim it.

title: The Hateful Eight
overview: In the dead of a Wyoming winter, a bounty hunter and his prisoner find shelter in a cabin currently inhabited by a collection of nefarious characters.
stars: ['Samuel L. Jackson', 'Kurt Russell', 'Jennifer Jason Leigh', 'Walton Goggins']

title: Madeo
overview: A mother desperately searches for the killer who framed her son for a girl's horrific murder.

title: La haine
overview: 24 hours in the lives of three young men in the French suburbs the day after a violent riot.

title: Un prophète
overview: A young Arab man is sent to a French prison.

title: Glengarry Glen Ross
overview: An examination of the machinations behind the scenes at a real estate office.

title: 12 Angry Men
overview: A jury holdout attempts to prevent a miscarriage of justice by forcing his colleagues to reconsider the evidence.

title: Training Day
overview: A rookie cop spends his first day as a Los Angeles narcotics officer with a rogue detective who isn't what he appears to be.
